---
import HomeLayout from '../../layouts/HomeLayout.astro';
---

<HomeLayout title="FAQ - Switch-Lit">
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>What is Switch-Lit?</h1>
      <p>
        Switch-Lit is a creative writing platform designed for turn-based collaborative fiction, poetry, and prose. 
        Each work becomes an imaginative conversation between any two creative writers: one starts, the other 
        responds in kind, and the narrative world comes alive via alternating chapters. The final results are 
        multi-perspective stories and genre-bending experiments that can read like collective dreams.
      </p>
      <p class="recognition">
        Launched publicly in 2024, Switch-Lit has been recognized as a 2025 SXSW Innovation Award Finalist 
        ("Connection and Communication" category), a featured panelist at Harvard University's inaugural 
        "Social Media Solutions for the Public Interest" workshop, and the Brooklyn Public Library's 
        Community Incubator Grant program.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Who is Switch-Lit for?</span>
            <span class="icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Switch-Lit is for creative writers, poets, and storytellers who want to explore collaborative fiction with a partner.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>How do I start a Switch-Lit story?</span>
            <span class="icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Visit our Start a Story page, configure your story settings, and invite a writing partner to begin your collaborative journey.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>What if I don't have a writing partner?</span>
            <span class="icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>You can still start a story! Select "No" when asked about having a writing partner, and we'll help you find one through our community features.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Why is there a limit of (3) three active stories?</span>
            <span class="icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>This limit ensures quality engagement and helps writers focus on their current collaborations without spreading themselves too thin.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>What are your submission guidelines?</span>
            <span class="icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>We welcome all genres and styles. Stories should be original, collaborative works created through our platform.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>How do I submit my story to Switch-Lit for publishing?</span>
            <span class="icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Once your story is complete, it will automatically be available in our library. You can also request featured consideration.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Can I submit a story not written on the Switch-Lit platform?</span>
            <span class="icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Currently, we only accept stories created through our collaborative platform to maintain the integrity of the turn-based process.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>What is your publishing and editorial process?</span>
            <span class="icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Stories are published automatically upon completion. Our editorial team may select exceptional works for featuring in our library.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Who owns the copyright to the story?</span>
            <span class="icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Copyright is shared between all collaborating writers. Each contributor retains rights to their individual chapters while granting shared rights to the complete work.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>I'm a literary editor. How can I use Switch-Lit?</span>
            <span class="icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Editors can browse our library for emerging talent, discover unique collaborative voices, and potentially scout new authors for publication.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>I'm a cultural programmer. How can I use Switch-Lit?</span>
            <span class="icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Contact us about partnership opportunities. We offer workshops, residencies, and collaborative events for cultural institutions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>I'm an educator or librarian. How can I use Switch-Lit?</span>
            <span class="icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Switch-Lit is perfect for creative writing classes and library programs. Contact us for educational discounts and group accounts.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Do you have a press and media kit?</span>
            <span class="icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes! Contact us at press@switch-lit.com for our complete press kit including logos, screenshots, and founder bios.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>How do I contact Switch-Lit?</span>
            <span class="icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Email us at hello@switch-lit.com or use the contact form on our Contact page. We'd love to hear from you!</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</HomeLayout>

<script>
  const faqItems = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item');
  
  faqItems.forEach(item => {
    const button = item.querySelector('.faq-question');
    const answer = item.querySelector('.faq-answer');
    
    button.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const isOpen = item.classList.contains('active');
      
      // Close all items
      faqItems.forEach(i => {
        i.classList.remove('active');
        i.querySelector('.faq-answer').style.maxHeight = '0';
        i.querySelector('.icon').textContent = '+';
      });
      
      // Open clicked item if it wasn't already open
      if (!isOpen) {
        item.classList.add('active');
        answer.style.maxHeight = answer.scrollHeight + 'px';
        button.querySelector('.icon').textContent = '−';
      }
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  .page-header {
    padding: var(--spacing-xxl) 0 var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .page-header p {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .recognition {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .faq-section {
    padding: 0 0 var(--spacing-xxl);
  }

  .faq-list {
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .faq-question {
    width: 100%;
    text-align: left;
    padding: var(--spacing-lg) 0;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .faq-question .icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .faq-answer {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq-answer p {
    padding-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .faq-item.active .faq-answer {
    max-height: 200px;
  }

  .faq-item.active .icon {
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }
</style>
